# Example Cursor Rule Template

This file demonstrates the **shape** of a Cursor rule (`.mdc`).

## When it applies

- `alwaysApply: false` means it only applies when Cursor decides it’s relevant.
- `globs` lets you scope it to certain files (e.g. `"**/*.md"`, `"src/**/*.ts"`).

## Example guidance (edit freely)

- Prefer small, reviewable changes over large rewrites.
- When adding new files, also update `README.md` if onboarding or usage changes.
- If you touch any workflow under `_bmad/`, keep filenames stable and avoid breaking step links.

## Notes

- This is intentionally generic and safe: it’s meant as a **template** your team can copy and customize.
